


#----------------------------------------------------------------------
# INDEX MODE

?           : help
F1          : manual to get started

b           : bounce active email
m           : new mail
a           : create an alias using the email sender of active email
s           : save current email in a new folder
r           : replay to active message
f           : forward active message
g           : group reply to active message
q           : quit
d           : mark active message for deletion
u           : undelete active message
w           : set flags of active message manually
G           : pop mails from mail server to spool file
o           : change sort email order in current mailbox
l           : limit display (filter display) based on pattern-matching

TAGS
t           : tag current message
T           : tag message matching
Ctrl-T      : untag message matching
;           : next command is applied to all tagged messages 
ex: ; d will mark for deletion all tagged messages

NAVIGATION
0-1         : jump to message number
=           : jump to message 1 (Home)
<tab>       : next new or unread message
/           : search message for pattern
<- ->       : prev / next message
up - down   : prev / next page 

c           : change to a different mailbox 
                - ! is inbox
                - =sent is sent folder
                - =lists/epics for mailing list
                - ? for list of folders
#---------------------------------------------------------------------- 
# PAGER MODE (WHILE READING EMAIL)

h           : toggle show-all-headers
^           : jump to beginning of message
-           : scroll up
<space>     : scroll down or go to next email
$           : jump to end of message
\           : toggle search coloring
Ctrl-u      : (macro) start urlview

#---------------------------------------------------------------------- 
# FLAGS

+           : message is to you and you only (no CC or other TO)
T           : addressed directly to me
F           : my email address is in the CC
C
r
U
D           : message marked for deletion
d           : message with attachment marked for deletion
N           : new unread message
*           : message is tagged
i
#---------------------------------------------------------------------- 
# PATTERN SEARCHIMG
#

Many of Mutt's commands allow you to specify a pattern to match (limit, tag-pattern, delete-pattern, etc.). There are several ways to select messages:

 ~A              all messages
~b PATTERN      messages which contain PATTERN in the message body
~B PATTERN      messages which contain PATTERN in the whole message
~c USER         messages carbon-copied to USER
~C PATTERN      message is either to: or cc: PATTERN
~D              deleted messages
~d [MIN]-[MAX]  messages with ``date-sent'' in a Date range
~E              expired messages
~e PATTERN      message which contains PATTERN in the ``Sender'' field
~F              flagged messages
~f USER         messages originating from USER
~h PATTERN      messages which contain PATTERN in the message header
~i ID           message which match ID in the ``Message-ID'' field
~L PATTERN      message is either originated or received by PATTERN
~l              message is addressed to a known mailing list
~m [MIN]-[MAX]  message in the range MIN to MAX
~n [MIN]-[MAX]  messages with a score in the range MIN to MAX
~N              new messages
~O              old messages
~p              message is addressed to you (consults $alternates)
~P              message is from you (consults $alternates)
~Q              messages which have been replied to
~R              read messages
~r [MIN]-[MAX]  messages with ``date-received'' in a Date range
~S              superseded messages
~s SUBJECT      messages having SUBJECT in the ``Subject'' field.
~T              tagged messages
~t USER         messages addressed to USER
~U              unread messages
~x PATTERN      messages which contain PATTERN in the `References' field
~z [MIN]-[MAX]  messages with a size in the range MIN to MAX
Where PATTERN, USER, ID, and SUBJECT are regular expressions.

ex: ~d 20/1/95-31/10 !(~t mutt|~c mutt) ~f emayssat
ex: ~d <1m                                                              # No space between < and 1m

